    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="279"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Italy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1892</hi>
                        </date>. (Received July 21.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Foster</hi>: I notified by cable to his
                    excellency the minister of foreign affairs the contents of yours of the 18th
                    instant, and also the note of the Acting Secretary of the Navy.</p>
                <p>In answer, his excellency cablegrams as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Willingly accepting courteous invitation I now order that the royal
                            cruiser ‘<hi rend="italic">Bausan</hi>’ be at New York in the beginning
                            of October.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I desire to assure you, and, through you, the Hon. Mr. Soley, of the intense
                    pleasure I feel in making you this communication.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fava.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
